For quite a time after her return from the maternity ward, echoes ofher pangs in the darkest corridors of my brain and a frightening stainedwindow at every turn--the afterimage of a wounded orifice--pursued me anddeprived me of all my vigor. When everything in me healed, and my lust forher pale enchantments rekindled, its volume and violence put an end to thebrave but essentially inept efforts she had been making to reestablish somesort of amorous harmony between us without departing one